  "prompt": "What is Alma Mater society?",
  "response": "The term \"Alma Mater Society\" generally refers to student organizations or societies within universities. These societies often serve as the official student government or association within the institution. They are typically responsible for representing the student body, organizing events, and facilitating communication between students and the university administration.\n\nOne of the most well-known Alma Mater Societies is at Queen's University in Kingston, Ontario, Canada. There, the Alma Mater Society (AMS) is one of the oldest student governments in Canada. It provides various services, organizes events, and advocates for student interests. While the specific responsibilities and structure of an Alma Mater Society can vary from one institution to another, their primary purpose is to enhance the student experience and uphold student interests.",
